column1: # raw.read.pairs: number of read pairs from the sequencer before any processing
# dual.unique.molecular.identifier.read.pairs: Number of read pairs for which both read 1 and read 2 match the expected 5′-N12CAGT sequence at the beginning of the read.
# number.of.raw.reads.used.in.consensus.reads: Number of reads (not read pairs) used in the generation of consensus reads.
# consensus.sequence.reads: number of consensus reads generated (from read pairs with the same unique molecular identifier sequenced at least twice). These are the reads which were input into breseq
